   <text>
      <body>
         <head type="date">
            <date when="1804-04-21">April 21, 1804</date>
         </head>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-04-21.01" ref="">
            <sp who="wc">
               <speaker>Clark</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date/>
               </ab>
               <p>Satturday 21St    rain all last night Slowley    a Cloudy morning
             some rain    river raised last night 12 Inches    at
          three oClock a Cannon was herd up the 
          <name type="place" key="Missouri River">Missouris</name>, Soon after 
          <name type="person" key="Chouteau, Jean Pierre">Mr. Choteau</name>arrived with 22
          Indians, we Saluted them and after Staying one [h]Our, 
          <name type="person" key="Lewis, Meriwether">Cap Lewis</name>&amp; myself Set out with
          them to 
          <name type="place" key="Saint Louis, Mo.">St Louis</name>, where we arrived before
          night.
          <ref target="n03042101" n="1"/>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
         <div type="entry" xml:id="lc.jrn.1804-04-21.02" ref="">
            <sp who="jo">
               <speaker>Ordway</speaker>
               <ab>
                  <date>
                     <hi rend="italic">Detachment Orders</hi>
                     <lb/>April 21st 1804.</date>
               </ab>
               <p>Dureing the absence of the Commanding officers at 
          <name type="place" key="Saint Louis, Mo.">St. Louis</name>the Party are to be under the
          immediate Command of 
          <name type="person" key="Ordway, John">Sergeant John Ordway</name>agreeable to the
          Orders of the 7th Instant</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="right">Signed
            <ref target="n03042102" n="2"/>
                     <lb/>
                     <name type="person" key="Clark, William">Wm. Clark</name>Capt</hi>
               </p>
            </sp>
         </div>
      </body>
      <back>
